---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '@/components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '@/components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Flow — Process transparency for agentic work · Kontour AI"
  description="Kontour Flow keeps AI and automation on the required path by making every important transition evidence-backed, inspectable, and resumable."
>
  <Nav active="flow" />

  <section class="contour-bg" style="
    padding: 10rem var(--spacing-page) 6rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-edge);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  ">
    <div style="
      position: absolute;
      top: 0;
      right: 10%;
      width: 680px;
      height: 460px;
      background: radial-gradient(ellipse at top right, rgba(126,179,232,0.055) 0%, transparent 68%);
      pointer-events: none;
    "></div>

    <div style="max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto; position: relative; z-index: 1;">
      <div style="
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 5rem;
        align-items: center;
      ">
        <div>
          <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
            <span class="trust-badge trust-badge--verified">v0.1</span>
            <span style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--color-chalk-3);">npm install -D @kontourai/flow</span>
          </div>

          <h1 class="animate-fade-up" style="
            font-family: var(--font-display);
            font-optical-sizing: auto;
            font-size: clamp(3.5rem, 6vw, 5.5rem);
            font-weight: 400;
            line-height: 1.15;
            letter-spacing: -0.03em;
            color: var(--color-chalk);
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
          ">Flow</h1>

          <p class="animate-fade-up delay-100" style="
            font-family: var(--font-mono);
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            letter-spacing: 0.12em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            color: var(--color-cobalt-2);
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
          ">process transparency for any required-path work</p>

          <p class="animate-fade-up delay-200" style="
            font-size: 1.05rem;
            color: var(--color-chalk-2);
            line-height: 1.7;
            max-width: 500px;
            margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
          ">
            Agents skip steps, accept weak evidence, summarize work as complete,
            and lose the thread after compaction. Flow is the small thing
            missing in the middle: a record of the required path, the evidence
            each gate expected, the evidence that was actually collected, and
            the exceptions that need explicit human trust. It does not replace
            the systems that run work. It explains why the work was allowed to
            advance.
          </p>

          <div class="animate-fade-up delay-300" style="display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; flex-wrap: wrap;">
            <a href="https://github.com/kontourai/flow" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-primary" data-umami-event="flow-hero-github">
              View on GitHub →
            </a>
            <a href="/surface" class="btn-ghost" data-umami-event="flow-hero-surface">
              Built with Surface
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="animate-fade-in delay-300">
          <div class="terminal">
            <div class="terminal-bar">
              <div class="terminal-dot"></div>
              <div class="terminal-dot"></div>
              <div class="terminal-dot"></div>
              <span style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.65rem; color: var(--color-chalk-3); margin-left: 0.5rem;">flow report — current run</span>
            </div>
            <div class="terminal-body">
              <p><span class="prompt">$ </span><span class="cmd">flow status run.dev-1847 --format summary</span></p>
              <br />
              <p class="info">  flow run: agent-dev-flow / feature-search-filters</p>
              <p class="muted">  current step: verify</p>
              <br />
              <p class="pass">  PASS  plan gate: acceptance criteria linked</p>
              <p class="pass">  PASS  implementation gate: scoped files changed</p>
              <p class="warn">  BLOCK verify gate: browser evidence missing</p>
              <p class="muted">        expected: tests, lint, screenshot, Veritas readiness</p>
              <br />
              <p>  next action: <span class="warn">run browser check before publish</span></p>
              <p class="muted">  continuation: resume from verify, not chat memory</p>
              <p class="muted">  report: .flow/runs/run.dev-1847/report.md</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="
    padding: 5rem var(--spacing-page);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-edge);
    background: var(--color-ink-1);
  ">
    <div style="max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <div class="label-sm" style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-cobalt-2);">Quickstart</div>
      <div class="terminal">
        <div class="terminal-bar">
          <div class="terminal-dot"></div>
          <div class="terminal-dot"></div>
          <div class="terminal-dot"></div>
          <span style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.65rem; color: var(--color-chalk-3); margin-left: 0.5rem;">flow quickstart</span>
        </div>
        <div class="terminal-body">
          <p><span class="prompt">$ </span><span class="cmd">npm install -D @kontourai/flow</span></p>
          <p><span class="prompt">$ </span><span class="cmd">npx flow init</span></p>
          <p><span class="prompt">$ </span><span class="cmd">npx flow start examples/agent-dev-flow.json --run-id dev-1847</span></p>
          <p><span class="prompt">$ </span><span class="cmd">npx flow attach-evidence dev-1847 --gate verify-gate \</span></p>
          <p><span class="cmd">    --file ./test-output.json --kind command</span></p>
          <p><span class="prompt">$ </span><span class="cmd">npx flow report dev-1847</span></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="padding: 6rem var(--spacing-page);">
    <div style="max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <div class="label-sm" style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">What Flow answers</div>

      <div style="
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));
        gap: 1rem;
      ">
        {[
          { q: 'What process path was required?', color: 'var(--color-chalk-2)' },
          { q: 'Which step is active now?', color: 'var(--color-chalk-2)' },
          { q: 'Which gate controls the next transition?', color: 'var(--color-cobalt-2)' },
          { q: 'What evidence does the gate expect?', color: 'var(--color-cobalt-2)' },
          { q: 'What evidence was actually collected?', color: 'var(--color-green)' },
          { q: 'Why was the transition allowed or blocked?', color: 'var(--color-gold)' },
          { q: 'Was an exception accepted, and by whom?', color: 'var(--color-red)' },
          { q: 'How should another agent resume?', color: 'var(--color-chalk-2)' },
        ].map(({ q, color }, i) => (
          <div key={i} style="
            display: flex;
            align-items: flex-start;
            gap: 1rem;
            padding: 1.25rem;
            background: var(--color-ink-1);
            border: 1px solid var(--color-edge);
            border-radius: 4px;
          ">
            <span style="
              font-family: var(--font-mono);
              font-size: 0.65rem;
              color: var(--color-chalk-3);
              padding-top: 2px;
              min-width: 1.5rem;
            ">0{i + 1}</span>
            <span style={`
              font-size: 0.9rem;
              color: ${color};
              line-height: 1.5;
            `}>{q}</span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="
    padding: 5rem var(--spacing-page);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-edge);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-edge);
    background: var(--color-ink-1);
  ">
    <div style="max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <div style="
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 4rem;
        align-items: center;
      ">
        <div>
          <div class="label-sm" style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-cobalt-2);">The difference</div>
          <h2 class="display-md" style="color: var(--color-chalk); margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
            A trace says what happened.<br />
            Flow says why it was enough.
          </h2>
          <p style="color: var(--color-chalk-2); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
            Observability is necessary, but a trace alone does not know whether
            the right verification happened, whether approval had enough context,
            or whether the agent skipped a required handoff.
          </p>
          <p style="color: var(--color-chalk-2); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 0;">
            Flow turns required paths into evidence-gated transitions. If the
            evidence is missing, the run blocks or routes back. If the user accepts
            the gap, the exception becomes part of the record.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="
          display: grid;
          grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
          gap: 1rem;
        ">
          {[
            { label: 'Flow Definition', detail: 'The required path and gate expectations', color: 'var(--color-cobalt-2)' },
            { label: 'Flow Run', detail: 'One concrete execution with state and history', color: 'var(--color-green)' },
            { label: 'Gate Evidence', detail: 'Tests, CI, traces, approvals, Veritas reports', color: 'var(--color-gold)' },
            { label: 'Flow Report', detail: 'Current state, blocked gates, next action', color: 'var(--color-chalk-2)' },
          ].map(({ label, detail, color }) => (
            <div key={label} style="
              background: var(--color-ink-2);
              border: 1px solid var(--color-edge);
              border-radius: 6px;
              padding: 1.25rem;
            ">
              <div style={`
                font-family: var(--font-mono);
                font-size: 0.7rem;
                color: ${color};
                margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
              `}>{label}</div>
              <div style="
                font-family: var(--font-mono);
                font-size: 0.65rem;
                color: var(--color-chalk-3);
                letter-spacing: 0.04em;
                line-height: 1.55;
              ">{detail}</div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="padding: 5rem var(--spacing-page); border-top: 1px solid var(--color-edge);">
    <div style="max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <div class="label-sm" style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">What Flow does not replace</div>

      <div style="
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
        gap: 1rem;
      ">
        {[
          { title: 'Workflow engines', body: 'Camunda, Temporal, Dapr, Inngest, and Trigger.dev can still run durable work. Flow records gate state and evidence.', color: 'var(--color-gold)' },
          { title: 'Agent frameworks', body: 'LangGraph, CrewAI, OpenAI Agents, Microsoft Agent Framework, and runtime SDKs can still execute agent loops.', color: 'var(--color-cobalt-2)' },
          { title: 'Observability', body: 'Phoenix, LangSmith, AgentOps, and OpenTelemetry can still store traces. Flow interprets traces against gate expectations.', color: 'var(--color-green)' },
          { title: 'Policy systems', body: 'OPA, security tools, and Veritas can still evaluate rules. Flow records their decisions as process evidence.', color: 'var(--color-red)' },
        ].map(({ title, body, color }) => (
          <div key={title} class="card" style="padding: 1.5rem; position: relative; overflow: hidden;">
            <div style={`
              position: absolute;
              top: 0;
              left: 0;
              right: 0;
              height: 2px;
              background: linear-gradient(90deg, ${color}, transparent);
            `}></div>
            <h3 style="
              font-family: var(--font-display);
              font-size: 1.25rem;
              font-weight: 400;
              color: var(--color-chalk);
              margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
              letter-spacing: -0.01em;
            ">{title}</h3>
            <p style="font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--color-chalk-3); line-height: 1.65;">{body}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="
    padding: 5rem var(--spacing-page);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-edge);
    background: var(--color-ink-1);
  ">
    <div style="max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <div style="
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.2fr;
        gap: 4rem;
        align-items: center;
      ">
        <div>
          <div class="label-sm" style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-gold);">Product line</div>
          <h2 class="display-md" style="color: var(--color-chalk); margin-bottom: 1rem;">
            One transparency stack.<br />Independent products.
          </h2>
          <p style="color: var(--color-chalk-2); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
            Surface makes claims inspectable. Flow makes process transitions
            inspectable. Flow Agents can use Flow to keep
            agents on track inside Codex, Claude Code, Kiro, GitHub Actions,
            and future runtimes.
          </p>
          <p style="color: var(--color-chalk-2); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.7;">
            The user sees a useful workflow. Underneath, each Kontour product
            contributes a focused trust primitive.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="terminal">
          <div class="terminal-bar">
            <div class="terminal-dot"></div>
            <div class="terminal-dot"></div>
            <div class="terminal-dot"></div>
            <span style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.65rem; color: var(--color-chalk-3); margin-left: 0.5rem;">kontour stack</span>
          </div>
          <div class="terminal-body">
            <p><span class="info">Surface</span>  claims, evidence, policies, trust snapshots</p>
            <p><span class="info">Flow</span>     steps, gates, transitions, exceptions, reports</p>
            <p><span class="info">Veritas</span>  repo standards, evidence checks, merge readiness</p>
            <p><span class="info">Flow Agents</span>     coming soon: agent-runtime distribution + work modes</p>
            <br />
            <p class="muted">  shared promise: Kontour AI shows the work behind AI.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer active="flow" />
</Layout>

<style>
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    section > div > div[style*="grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr"] {
      display: flex !important;
      flex-direction: column !important;
    }
    section > div > div[style*="grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.2fr"] {
      display: flex !important;
      flex-direction: column !important;
    }
    section > div > div[style*="grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr)"] {
      display: flex !important;
      flex-direction: column !important;
    }
  }
</style>
